      ],
      "name": "t:sections.custom-liquid.presets.name",
      "settings": {
        "custom_liquid": "<div id=\"do_gaba\" class=\"card card__text \n           gutter--xlarge  \n           \n        spacing--large remove-empty-space\"> \n\n<div class=\"flex-display\" style=\"align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\">\n<div style=\"margin-right: 50px;\">\n<div class=\"h3\">Do GABA Supplements Work? A Critical View</div>\n<p >Several drugs mimic or increase GABA in the brain, including  benzodiazepines and gabapentin, but taking GABA directly as a supplement won’t  work for most people. This is because GABA is made in the brain and cannot easily get across the blood-brain barrier (BBB) when taken directly, despite what your  supplement company may tell you.</p>\n\n<p >Remember the “problem” above? Well, this is it! Another problem is that most of these pharmaceutical drugs that modulate GABA receptors are highly addictive and/or can induce tolerance and withdrawal when you stop them. But there’s good news! Much safer solutions are available, including N-nicotinoyl-GABA and Kava, which enhance GABA in novel ways (more below!).</p>\n</div>\n<div><div class=\"grid grid--layout \"><div class=\"article__meta-author\">\n                \n\n                <div class=\"card__icon-margin card__icon-size--regular\" id=\"element-image_KN7exw-0\"><figure class=\"lazy-image lazy-image--animation lazyloaded\" data-ratio=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 100%\">\n                      <img src=\"//troscriptions.com/cdn/shop/files/scott-sherr-updated.jpg?crop=center&amp;height=120&amp;v=1679455060&amp;width=120\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"\n                          //troscriptions.com/cdn/shop/files/scott-sherr-updated.jpg?crop=center&amp;height=120&amp;v=1679455060&amp;width=120 120w\n                           ,//troscriptions.com/cdn/shop/files/scott-sherr-updated.jpg?crop=center&amp;height=240&amp;v=1679455060&amp;width=240 240w, \n                           ,//troscriptions.com/cdn/shop/files/scott-sherr-updated.jpg?crop=center&amp;height=360&amp;v=1679455060&amp;width=360 360w, \n                           ,//troscriptions.com/cdn/shop/files/scott-sherr-updated.jpg?crop=center&amp;height=480&amp;v=1679455060&amp;width=480 480w, \n                           ,//troscriptions.com/cdn/shop/files/scott-sherr-updated.jpg?crop=center&amp;height=640&amp;v=1679455060&amp;width=640 640w, \n                        \" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 474px) 120px, 160px\" width=\"120\" height=\"120\" onload=\"this.parentNode.classList.add('lazyloaded')\">\n                    </figure></div>\n\n                <div class=\"spacing--small remove-empty-space\"><div>\n                      <h2 class=\"h5\" style=\"margin-bottom:0;\"><span class=\"text-animation--underline\">Dr. Scott Sherr</span></h2>\n                    </div><div class=\"text-size--small text-color--opacity\" style=\"min-width: 250px; max-width: 350px;\">Dr. Scott Sherr is a Board-Certified Internal Medicine Physician Certified to Practice Health Optimization Medicine (HOMe), a specialist in Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy (HBOT), and COO of Troscriptions (a Smarter Not Harder company). His clinical telepractice includes HOMe as its foundation alongside an integrative approach to HBOT that includes cutting edge and dynamic HBOT protocols, comprehensive testing (using the HOMe framework), targeted supplementation, personal practices, synergistic technologies (new, ancient, psychedelic), and more.</div></div>\n              </div>\n          </div></div>\n</div>\n</div>",
