            "custom_liquid": "<br><ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; list-style-position: inside; margin-top: -10px; padding-left: 20px;\">\n  <li><a href=\"https://troscriptions.com/blogs/main/nicotinoyl-gaba\" style=\"  text-decoration: underline;\">N-nicotinoyl-GABA</a>, a vitamin B3 attached to a GABA molecule, easily crosses the BBB and increases GABA  directly. This is called orthosteric modulation of the GABA receptor.</li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://troscriptions.com/blogs/main/kava\" style=\"  text-decoration: underline;\">Kava</a> binds to the GABA receptor at a separate site (allosteric modulation) and increases the binding of  GABA.</li>\n</ul>"
