    "faq_v2_x9Wxfn": {
      "type": "faq-v2",
      "blocks": {
        "question_gnVw4e": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How does GABA work?",
            "text": "<p>GABA works by binding to GABA receptors in the brain, inhibiting neural activity, which can lead to decreased anxiety, enhanced mood,  better sleep, and a feeling of calm. Supplements that increase GABA are a great option for those looking to naturally manage stress and anxiety levels. But remember: GABA itself doesn’t cross the blood- brain barrier. Tro Calm and Tro Zzz have proven ingredients that enhance the GABA system in novel ways, easily crossing the blood-brain barrier. </p>",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "question_V877CB": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How long does a GABA supplement stay in my system?",
            "text": "<p>Supplements that increase GABA have effects that last several hours, with variability depending on individual metabolism and the specific GABA supplement dosage. Most users feel improvements within 4 to 6 hours after ingestion.  Remember that most direct GABA supplementation wil have no or little effect. </p>",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "question_XkfgbW": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can GABA supplements cause liver damage?",
            "text": "<p>There is no significant evidence indicating that supplements that increase GABA directly cause liver damage when taken at recommended doses. However, please consult your healthcare provider before starting/stopping any supplements or medications.</p>",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "question_VzbtiT": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does GABA cross the blood-brain barrier?",
            "text": "<p>GABA's ability to cross the blood-brain barrier is limited, raising questions about the effectiveness  of some GABA supplements for anxiety, stress, sleep, or any other purported benefit. This has led to the exploration of compounds that increase GABA indirectly, such as Kava (in Tro Calm) Honokiol, and Agarain (in Tro Zzz).</p>",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "question_HqyNiV": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is it OK to take GABA regularly?",
            "text": "<p>Regularly taking supplements that increase GABA or having foods that contain GABA is considered safe for most people, especially when following the recommended supplement  dosage. Consistent use may lead to sustained benefits for managing stress and enhancing sleep  quality. </p>",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "question_qADQbF": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the downside of taking GABA?",
            "text": "<p>The primary downside to taking supplements that increase GABA might include potential side effects such as drowsiness, digestive discomfort, headaches, and lowering of blood pressure. Furthermore, the challenge of  crossing the blood-brain barrier will affect the efficacy of direct GABA supplemenation. </p>",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "question_M8GpTe": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does GABA make you sleepy?",
            "text": "<p>GABA taken directly will unlikely have a major effect as GABA does not cross the blood-brain barrier. However, ingredients in Tro Calm were designed to be relaxing and not sedating, using several ingredients that enhance GABA in novel ways. Tro Zzz contains GABA-enhancing ingredients that will make you sleep...that's why it is for sleep! </p>",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        }
      },
